    <item>
      <title>Grandma&amp;#039;s Toilet - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 02 Aug 2025 03:18:36 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8896" class="post-8896 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Grandma&amp;#8217;s Toilet&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Monday (July 27th) was Ketchup&amp;#8217;s birthday. I bought her a cube light from Nook&amp;#8217;s Cranny, and then I customized it to be red. I wrapped it up, and gave it to her as her birthday present.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Ketchup: Whaaat?! You got me a cube light?!" class="wp-image-8898" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She said she wasn&amp;#8217;t expecting it, and she said she&amp;#8217;d never forget it&amp;#8230;but she never said she liked it. Oops. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Louie was also at the party, and he said everyone was in party-flex mode. Whatever that means.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Louie: Today is Ketchup's big day, I'm cranky. Everyone's in party-flex mode!" class="wp-image-8899" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Out in the rain, I had a chat with my buddy Bob. We were standing by a toilet, and Bob said he makes sure that no one sits there.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Bob: I always make sure nobody's sitting on that tankless toilet." class="wp-image-8900" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That&amp;#8217;s because it&amp;#8217;s reserved for his grandma! Why would he make his grandma sit on a toilet out in the open, possibly in the rain? 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Bob: I like to keep it empty so there's someplace for Grandma to sit if she comes to visit!" class="wp-image-8901" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Peanut, she told me she invented a new type of D.I.Y. called ASTDIFM:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Peanut: I've invented a cool new kind of DIY called ASTDIFM. It means, Ask Someone To Do It For Me." class="wp-image-8902" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I thought she was about to ask &lt;em&gt;me &lt;/em&gt;to do something for her, but she didn&amp;#8217;t. I left her house quickly, before she could change her mind. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;During golden hour on Wednesday, Ankha asked me to catch a miyama stag for her. Fortunately, I already had one in my pockets. I handed it over, and she rewarded me with a snorkel mask. I actually decided to put it on, for no particular reason other than it seemed like a summery thing to wear. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="Ankha: You've more than earned this snorkel mask! It's the least I could do." class="wp-image-8903" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;It really is.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I saw a balloon present flying through the top of a bamboo tree. It was able to pass through as if the tree wasn&amp;#8217;t really there.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="650" height="367" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/Array" alt="A balloon present flies through bamboo." class="wp-image-8897" sizes="auto, (max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I shot it down and found a zen light inside.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/01/grandmas-toilet/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-01T23:18:36-04:00"&gt;August 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-01T23:19:49-04:00"&gt;August 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ketchup-bday2025-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Moss Ball, Good Call - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Aug 2025 03:11:47 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18299" class="post-18299 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Moss Ball, Good Call&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I visited Rolf to find that Lolly was also visiting. But her dialogue was a bit confusing, especially out of context.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Lolly: Pete is here! It must be hard to deliver all the letters in town. We definitely keep him busy!" class="wp-image-18300" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mira asked me for some new furniture, saying anything would do. So I decided to shop around and buy something special for her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Harvey: Ah! So you're interested in my moss ball..." class="wp-image-18301" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I took the moss ball over to Mira, and she seemed to like it. But even if she didn&amp;#8217;t like it, I&amp;#8217;m sure it&amp;#8217;ll grow on her. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Mira: Oh! A moss ball? Good call!" class="wp-image-18302" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The most surprising part of this exchange was my reward. She gave me a cyclommatus stag! That&amp;#8217;s an 8,000-bell reward! For a moss ball! Wow!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Mira: All right... Here. Take my old cyclommatus stag if you want. It's all yours!" class="wp-image-18303" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Jeremiah asked me to play a game of hide-and-seek. He gave me ten minutes to find him, Mira, and Molly. I found Jeremiah pretty much instantly.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Hide-and-seek start! / Jeremiah: Dark. I guess yo..." class="wp-image-18304" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;About two minutes later, I found Mira trying to hide behind the zen bell.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Mira tries to hid behind the zen bell during a game of hide-and-seek." class="wp-image-18305" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And shortly after that, I found Molly behind Jeremiah&amp;#8217;s house. They all stayed on the eastern side of the map, so I didn&amp;#8217;t have trouble finding them all in less than three minutes total.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Molly hides behind Jeremiah's house." class="wp-image-18306" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My prize for winning the game was&amp;#8230;a mop. Real exciting, huh? It&amp;#8217;s okay though, I didn&amp;#8217;t let it dampen my spirits.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Jeremiah: To commemorate your win, I'll give you my mop!" class="wp-image-18307" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later gave the mop to Mira when she asked me for furniture (again). She gave me a lovely table in return.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;During the game of hide-and-seek, I found a lost item on the ground. I eventually returned it to its owner, Boots. He said it was his pole-vaulting glove! Yeah, I don&amp;#8217;t think he could pole vault without some help. In fact, he&amp;#8217;d need a lot of gator aid.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Boots: Oh, yeah! My pole-vaulting glove!" class="wp-image-18308" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He said it was still damp from his hand sweat? Okay, that&amp;#8217;s kinda gross.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Boots: Feels a bit damp from hand sweat... Yup, it's mine all right!" class="wp-image-18309" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He rewarded me with a foosball table.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, my old buddy Rod was camping out at the campsite. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/Array" alt="Rod, at the campsite: Hey! Do you think it's OK if I camp here for a while?" class="wp-image-18310" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Sure thing!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It was nice to see him again, but of course I don&amp;#8217;t have a vacancy in my town.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/07/31/moss-ball-good-call/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-31T23:11:47-04:00"&gt;July 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-31T23:16:00-04:00"&gt;July 31, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/20250728_HNI_0080.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Lunar Leap Month 3rd - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Jul 2025 22:36:04 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5987" class="post-5987 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Lunar Leap Month 3rd&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;When I played on Wednesday, I found a goodbye letter from Puddles in the mail (unfortunately).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Guess what, Jeff! I realize this is a little cuckoo, but I've decided to move. Have I lost it? No!!! I've just got to try to get a fresh start. I don't even know where I'm going yet! See ya! -Puddles" class="wp-image-5990" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On the bulletin board, I saw the notice that morning aerobics starts on July 25th, and it runs through the end of August. Moments later, Candi quizzed me on that exact fact. She asked which event starts on July 25th, so obviously I knew the answer. Candi teased a reward, but then laughingly told me there was no prize.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Candi: So, let's see what's behind curtain number one... Ah ha ha ha ha! There's no prize! Get serious!" class="wp-image-5991" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A few minutes later, Belle asked me the same question! Since I wanted to see how she&amp;#8217;d react (and since I knew there wasn&amp;#8217;t a prize anyway), I chose to answer that the fireworks festival was the event that runs every day in summer. As you might expect, my stupidity angered her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Belle: ...Hello!? Earth to Jeff! Get your head out of the clouds and think a little, cuddles!" class="wp-image-5992" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rocco asked if I&amp;#8217;d rather play golf or watch golf, and I wasn&amp;#8217;t really interested in either. But I told him I&amp;#8217;d rather watch it, and he compared me to a lazy slug. Nice.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Rocco: You Seriously? You just like sitting on your behind like a lazy slug and watching?" class="wp-image-5993" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Down on the beach, I found Gulliver passed out. I tried to release a cockroach onto him, but it flew away instead. After I woke up the sleeping gull, he gave me a Chinese lion.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I met up with Baabara, she was talking about Wendell. She didn&amp;#8217;t like the fact that he begs for food, and yet he&amp;#8217;s picky about what he&amp;#8217;ll eat.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Baabara: Just thinking about picky vagrants makes me so mad I want to scratch, daahling!" class="wp-image-5994" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Sydney has a new neighbor, and I was happy to meet her: It&amp;#8217;s Coco the coconut/gyroid rabbit!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Coco: Eeeeek!" class="wp-image-5995" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Welcome to Forest, Coco! I hope you&amp;#8217;ll stick around a while!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Puck complimented me on my nice clothes, and he said he was my number one fan. That was kinda funny, because I was wearing the No. 1 shirt.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Puck: If anyone gives you flack about your getup, lemme know. I'm your number one...um... fashion fan..." class="wp-image-5996" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I returned to talk to Coco more, and she told me a friend gave her a bus stop that she can&amp;#8217;t use. 🚌&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Coco: A friend of mine gave me a bus stop the other day, but I can't really use it." class="wp-image-5997" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I thought she was going to give it to me for free, but she actually wanted 2,820 bells for it. I didn&amp;#8217;t want it that bad, so I kept on walking.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played again today, and Ursala told me about the lunar calendar. She said that today is &amp;#8220;Leap Month 3rd.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Ursala: Today's July 27th, but according to the lunar calendar, it's leap month 3rd." class="wp-image-5999" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t have an option to question that, but she assumed I had a problem with it and wanted to &amp;#8220;start something.&amp;#8221; 🙄&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Ursala: What? What do you mean, that makes no sense?!" class="wp-image-6000" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Ursala: Are you saying you've got a problem with the lunar calendar? Are you trying to start something!?" class="wp-image-6001" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I never want to start anything with you. I just want to finish it&amp;#8230;including this conversation. Bye.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Candi reminded me that if you borrow the Able Sisters&amp;#8217; sewing equipment (by linking a Game Boy Advance), you can design patterns for free. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Candi: Jeff! You didn't know? You don't have to pay for your design if you borrow their sewing equipment!" class="wp-image-6002" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s been a while since I&amp;#8217;ve designed patterns in this game, so I forgot what they charged for a pattern. So I headed over there and asked Mabel. She told me it costs 350 bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/Array" alt="Mabel: Oh, you want to create your own design? Great! It'll cost 350 bells for materials, of course. That's OK, right?" class="wp-image-6003" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/07/27/lunar-leap-month-3rd/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-27T18:36:04-04:00"&gt;July 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-27T18:38:19-04:00"&gt;July 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ac-puddles-out-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fang Raised by Wolves - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Jul 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13520" class="post-13520 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Fang Raised by Wolves&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday night, Antonio told me he was planning on moving out of town. But I told him to stay, and he agreed&amp;#8230;even though he didn&amp;#8217;t exactly like me telling him what to do.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="Antonio: Well, up my nose... That...that stinks! But fine, I get it!" class="wp-image-13525" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;It stinks up your nose? Or that&amp;#8217;s just where you smell it?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In another part of town, I saw a scorpion casually fall off a cliff, and act like nothing happened! I was able to walk over and catch it without a problem. That&amp;#8217;s not something I see every day.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I ran into Antonio again, he was talking about something his friend showed him, that made him jealous. Um, what?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="Antonio: AGGHHH! One of my buds was showing his off to me the other day, and it made me so jealous, I went feral!" class="wp-image-13526" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Fortunately, he was talking about a saw stag beetle. He wanted to buy one that I had in my pockets, and I agreed to sell it to him for 1,644 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Down closer to the beach, I saw a bug on a tree&amp;#8230;but it was obscured by another tree, and I wasn&amp;#8217;t sure what it was. Biskit was walking close to it, so I tried to catch it before Biskit scared it away. It ended up being a golden stag (my favorite)! I&amp;#8217;m glad I caught it in time!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="Jeff, after catching a golden stag: Whoa!!" class="wp-image-13527" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My Monday night bug hunt netted me 250k in an hour of playing. As for my savings total balance, I&amp;#8217;ve decided not to give updates on it until the summer is over. I&amp;#8217;m certainly going to meet and exceed my original goal, and I already have another goal in mind. But I&amp;#8217;d rather have it be a surprise at the end of the summer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday night, Monty thought he was sharing some shocking news when he told me that Fang was raised by wolves. And normally I&amp;#8217;d accuse him of telling me a &lt;em&gt;pack &lt;/em&gt;of lies. But Fang &lt;em&gt;is &lt;/em&gt;a wolf, so this isn&amp;#8217;t exactly surprising. Nice try though, Monty. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="Monty: Take Fang, for example. Did you know he was raised by wolves?" class="wp-image-13523" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My Tuesday night bug hunt netted me another 300k in an hour and a half.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t play again until today. At the Roost tonight, I asked for a random song. K.K. performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Dirge&amp;#8221; for me. It&amp;#8217;s a little early for spooky music season, so I&amp;#8217;m not sure if this was just a &lt;em&gt;grave &lt;/em&gt;mistake, or if K.K. is getting a &lt;em&gt;monster &lt;/em&gt;head start on Halloween.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Dirge." class="wp-image-13528" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Marina was the latest villager to want out of town, but I told her to stick around. It took several attempts, but I was eventually able to change her mind.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/Array" alt="Marina: What's wrong with me?! The answer is so obvious! I'm going to stay, blurp!" class="wp-image-13529" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I went on my third bug hunt of the week tonight. In a 70-minute session, I earned over 210,000 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If you enjoy the bug hunting videos, I posted a Wild World one earlier today. Check it out if you&amp;#8217;re interested, &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0FKF4uNR8oU" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/07/26/fang-raised-by-wolves/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-26T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;July 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-27T01:33:00-04:00"&gt;July 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/RUU_8292-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>July Bug-Off 2025 - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 26 Jul 2025 20:09:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8885" class="post-8885 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;July Bug-Off 2025&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I was diving in the ocean on Tuesday, looking for Gullivarrr&amp;#8217;s phone. When I found a scallop instead, Pascal popped up. I got this screenshot of both special characters in the background, and I like how it turned out. 🙂&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Me, as Pascal and Gullivarrr show up in the background: I got a scallop!" class="wp-image-8886" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The 2nd Bug-Off of the year was held today (Saturday, July 26th). I started up a round, and I caught a rare Queen Alexandra&amp;#8217;s birdwing 40 seconds into the competition. Nice!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="I caught a Queen Alexandra's birdwing! Gotta keep this up!" class="wp-image-8887" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I caught 11 bugs (for a total of 13 points), but I felt like I could&amp;#8217;ve done better. Mainly because I wasted too much time chasing a darner dragonfly that sent me on a wild goose chase back and forth across the river. 😆 Still, those 11 bugs netted me 10,080 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So I decided to play another round&amp;#8230;but I again caught 11 bugs (and scored 13 points). Even though I caught my last bug with 5 seconds on the clock, my net still exploded as time expired. Oof.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="The game, as my net fell apart: Bug-Off is over!" class="wp-image-8888" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I quickly went to shoot down a balloon present that I saw during the timed competition&amp;#8230;and then my slingshot blew up too. Oof.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Oh no! It's the end of the line for my trusty slingshot..." class="wp-image-8889" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t judge me, Bones.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;To add insult to injury, the present only contained five pieces of clay. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After crafting some new tools, I went back to Flick. I sold him this batch of 11 bugs for just 4,020 bells this time. But I also redeemed 30 of my 33 points for prizes: a toy centipede, a bug wand, and a toy cockroach.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Bug-Off was stressing out some of my villagers, especially poor Peanut here. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Peanut: I meditated...but not enough!" class="wp-image-8890" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You&amp;#8217;re doing great, Peanut!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My two &amp;#8220;A&amp;#8221; named villagers (Agent S and Ankha) were the only two not outside participating in the event. Ankha told me that she thinks wallpaper is back in style, and I wondered if she meant hieroglyphics. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Ankha: Some people might disagree, but I think wallpaper is back in style." class="wp-image-8891" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, Static was sick with a cold. I gave him some medicine, and he rewarded me with some full-body tights. That&amp;#8217;s kind of a personal gift, but me and him are really &lt;em&gt;tight&lt;/em&gt;. 😛&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Gullivarrr sent me a pirate barrel on Wednesday.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;C.J. was in town Wednesday, and I sold him 21 fish for 352,500 bells. 💰💰💰&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Thursday, I sold 32 bugs to Flick for 231,000 bells. 💰💰&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/07/26/july-bug-off-2025/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-26T16:09:12-04:00"&gt;July 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-26T16:11:03-04:00"&gt;July 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/scallop-pascal-gulliver-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Drift, Pippy to Battle? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Jul 2025 21:52:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8272" class="post-8272 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Drift, Pippy to Battle?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I listened in on a conversation between Pippy and Drift. Pippy asked if Drift has been watching her!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="Pippy, to Drift: Hey! You've been watching me, haven't you?!" class="wp-image-8278" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Drift admitted to it, because he wants to prepare for an epic battle against her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="Drift: Of course! How else do you expect me to prepare for my epic battle against you?" class="wp-image-8274" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pippy was confused by this, because she had no plans of being in a battle against him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="Pippy: Epic battle?! Uhhhh, haven't you noticed that I'm a cute girl, not a gladiator?" class="wp-image-8273" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So, she thought he was a psycho. And she&amp;#8217;s probably right. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="Pippy: What kind of a psycho are you, li'l hare?!" class="wp-image-8275" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Drift tried to justify it by saying he imagined himself losing to Pippy. I don&amp;#8217;t know, my villagers are just weird.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I thought I&amp;#8217;d try a late-night bug hunt, like the ones I do in &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EFnEZqWVqjg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;City Folk&lt;/a&gt;. I started before 10:30 p.m., so I&amp;#8217;d be able to hunt for half an hour before the shop closed. But in that span, I wasn&amp;#8217;t finding many rare bugs. I caught a rainbow stag, a goliath beetle, and an atlas beetle&amp;#8230;but everything else was a 1,000-bell bug or less! &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I only made 36k in 30 minutes, and I probably could&amp;#8217;ve done better than that by just gathering fruit! So I won&amp;#8217;t be posting a video of that. However, after the clock struck 11:00, I was suddenly seeing more (and better) bugs! So I decided that I would try again Thursday night, but at 11:00 instead of 10:30. The bad thing is that I&amp;#8217;d be unable to sell my catches, so I could only fill up my pockets once. I recorded a gameplay session of that&amp;#8230; &lt;em&gt;Update: Here it is.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: Wild World - Late-Night Bug Hunt Gameplay (30 mins.) 2025" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0FKF4uNR8oU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Filbert told me he had been looking for a popeyed goldfish. I thought this was going to be a request (or a competition), but it was just dialogue. Apparently, he felt a bit dumb because he hasn&amp;#8217;t been able to find one yet. Aww, poor guy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="Filbert: It's like a contest between me and the fish to see who's dumber, bucko." class="wp-image-8276" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I saw a big fish shadow in the river, and I fished out a giant snakehead. That&amp;#8217;s a fish I don&amp;#8217;t see very often! I think I best remember it as the last fish I caught in the GameCube game (when I first &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oG190uJ-vhM" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;completed my fish collection&lt;/a&gt;, in 2007).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array" alt="I caught a giant snakehead! ACK! It's got a huge head!" class="wp-image-8277" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I actually found two items in the recycle bin at town hall today: a kiddie stereo and a Nintendo bench. Nice!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Curt has still been sick this week, so I gave him more medicine Wednesday, Thursday, and again today. Get well soon, Curt!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/07/25/drift-pippy-to-battle/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-07-25T17:52:23-04:00"&gt;July 25, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-07-26T11:10:09-04:00"&gt;July 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
